Gold-Filled Chain Care Tips

Gold-filled material should not fade or tarnish as easily as others. However,

to make your gold-filled jewelry last longer, we recommend you to

(1) Clean your gold-filled chain using mild soap and pat dry with a clean,

soft cotton cloth before first use.

(2) Avoid contact with lotions, cosmetics, perfumes, sunscreens, or other chemicals.

(3) Store it separately in a closed, airtight storage bag (ziplock bag, for example).

(4) It's okay to shower with it on, which helps clean it, but remember to dry it

with a soft cloth afterward.

(5) Once it darkens, remove the tarnish with mild soap immediately. Give it a scrub

with an ultrasoft toothbrush and gently dry it afterward. Then it will look as new as ever.

(6) Clean it, dry it, and then keep it in an airtight bag if you won't wear it for a long time.

FEEDING GUIDELINES

Raw-fed cats typically eat between 2% - 4% of their body weight daily.
The average adult cat will eat 4.50z/128g per day—adjust up or down
based on your cat's size, activity level, and age.

Kittens should be fed as much as they want, at least 4 times a day
until 4 months of age, when the feedings can be reduced to 3 times a
day. As the growth slows down, please reduce the amount of food
accordingly. Pregnant and lactating cats will generally eat double the
average daily requirements, and should have a constant supply
of food.

Please note the above are general guidelines, please consult your
veterinarian for your cat's specific daily nutritional requirements.

We recommend dividing the daily food requirement into at least
three meals per day. The timing of meals does not need to be evenly
spaced: most feed in the morning, early evening, and before bed.

Itis important to feed a varied diet that includes at least three
different proteins. For more information, please visit our website.

WARNING: Use only as directed. This is a premix that turns boneless
meat into a complete and balanced food. EZComplete fur Cats is not
intended for use with any already balanced cat food and should not
be used in any commercial cat food. Do not use EZComplete fur Cats
as a vitamin or with any other nutritional supplement.

Do not thaw at room temperature. Thaw in refrigerator or for rapid thawing for immediate use, place container in a bow! of lukewarm
water. When thawed, mix and serve. Feed within half an hour of serving. For cooked meals use the rapid thawing method.
